cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SC. 

The paper deals with designing and analyzing protocols for verifying computations on matrices over a ring of univariate polynomials, which involves concepts from computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and scientific computing (cs.SC). The focus on minimizing communication cost suggests that cs.CC and cs.IT are the most likely categories, followed by cs.DS and cs.SC, while cs.LG is less likely but still possible given the use of randomized protocols.
